name: Citizen Ghost #1
description:
Based on the Real Ghostbusters episode Citizen Ghost this is the first of four Glow in the Dark prints featuring the Ghostbusters possessed uniforms. 

To activate the glow charge the print under any normal household light.

The print is a three colour hand pulled screen print on 150 gsm acid-free Norfolk cartridge paper and is limited to an edition of 100.

All editions are signed and numbered by the artist with an image area of 22 x 30cm, printed on A3 paper.

name: Diamond Head
description:
Discovered at the North Magnetic Pole by Professor Maboul in 1912, Diamond Head is believed to direct earths magnetic field towards an as yet undiscovered being at the South Magnetic Pole.

The print is a four colour hand pulled screen print on 150 gsm acid-free Norfolk cartridge paper. 

This is an open ended edition and each print is signed by the artist.

The first run is Grey, Blue, Red and Black with colour variations to follow. 

Frame not included.

name: The Twins
description:
The Twins see the beginning and end of time simultaneously, forever aware that they cannot alter the chain of events that unfold before their ever watchful eyes.

The print is a three colour hand pulled screen print on 150 gsm acid-free Norfolk cartridge paper.
This is an open ended edition and each print is signed by the artist.

Frame not included.

name: Slimer
description:
Without a doubt Ghostbusters is one of the greatest comedies of all time and to show my appreciation I will be working on a series of GB screen prints. So i've decided to start with Slimer and am currently working on Sandman from Dream Me a Dream. If you have any other suggestions I would love to hear them. Just leave a message on my blog: 
http://aka-triffid.blogspot.com/

The print is a three colour hand pulled screen print on 150 gsm acid-free Norfolk cartridge paper and is limited to an edition of 100.

All editions are signed and numbered by the artist and the print is A3 with an image size of 16x19cm.

Frame not included.

name: Gatchaman
description:
This is the first print in a series of 5 featuring Ken from the 1970's japanese television show Gatchaman (or Battle of the Planets in America and England) the rest of the team will follow throughout 2011. 

The print is a four colour hand pulled screen print on 150 gsm acid-free Norfolk cartridge paper and is limited to an edition of 100.

I have also printed 10 very rare chaser prints which will be randomly inserted into orders. They will be in addition to your purchase and are classed as a Phoenix Edition.

All editions are signed and numbered by the artist, measuring A3 with a print size of 13x18cm.

Frame not included.
